COMMENTS: This or Tib. C.I used by Henry Bourchier in 1623 when he wrote to James Ussher saying that he was collating ‘Sir Robert Cotton's copy’ of the Ecclesiastical History with ‘Commelyn’s edition ..?: Elrington, Works of Ussher, XV, p. 188.

QUOTE_TRANSCRIPTION: Either A.XIV  or Tib. C.II was handed  on by Ward  to          Ussher  in 1624
COMMENTS: When doing so, he asked Ussher to return it to him, rather than Cotton, ‘for that I would keep it till Sir Robert restore a book of mine, which he had of Mr. Patrick Young’: Elrington, Works of Ussher, XV, p. 229, letter of 2 January, 1624/5.
